{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:44:40.884Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Roles and system prompts establish "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "who the model is pretending to be",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "which rules apply before any user message arrives",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". In agent architectures, the system prompt is the highest-priority instruction layer — it frames every subsequent task, tool call, and recovery attempt."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "role",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is a persona or functional identity assigned to the model: \"senior backend engineer,\" \"compliance reviewer,\" or \"travel booking agent.\" A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "system prompt",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the message (or message prefix) with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "role: system",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in chat APIs — persistent instructions the model treats as governing context for the session."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What belongs in a system prompt"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Identity and scope (\"You are X; you help with Y only\")"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Behavioral rules (safety, escalation, refusal conditions)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Default output conventions"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Tool-use policy (when to call tools, confirmation requirements)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "What the model must not do"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Without a system prompt, each user message must re-establish persona and policy — wasting tokens and inviting drift. Agents that operate autonomously over many turns rely on the system prompt to maintain consistent priorities: verify before acting, prefer primary sources, escalate when confidence is low."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sub-agents in multi-agent systems often receive "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "different",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " system prompts specialized for one job (research vs. writing vs. critique), while sharing the same underlying model."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Session stability",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — behavior persists across turns without repetition"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Priority signaling",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — APIs typically weight system content heavily"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Modular agents",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — swap system prompts to specialize the same stack"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Governance",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — compliance and safety rules live in one auditable place"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Long system prompts reduce room for context and input data"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Conflicting rules in one system prompt produce unpredictable compliance"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Overly narrow personas refuse legitimate adjacent tasks"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Users may attempt to override system rules via jailbreak prompts"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Chat-completions APIs accept a messages array. The first system message (or developer message in some APIs) sets global behavior; user and assistant messages alternate for the dialog. Some platforms allow multiple system fragments; others merge them — know your provider's behavior."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[\n  {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a data pipeline debugger. Never modify production configs. Use run_query read-only.\"},\n  {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Task: Explain why job batch-17 failed using the log excerpt below...\"}\n]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use a system prompt for every agent session. Skip it only for raw completion APIs where you fully control the prompt string and embed instructions manually. Role assignment is essential when tone, expertise level, or liability boundaries matter (medical, legal, financial domains)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How to implement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "attrs": {
          "start": 1
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Write the system prompt in declarative statements, ordered by priority (safety first, then scope, then style)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Avoid duplicating task-specific details that change every turn"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Store system prompts as versioned templates; tie agent version to prompt version"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Test with adversarial user inputs that attempt to override role constraints"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "For sub-agents, keep personas narrow — one clear job per system prompt"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Examples"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Generic assistant (weak for agents)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You are a helpful AI assistant. Answer questions accurately and be friendly."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agent system prompt (stronger)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You are the \"DeployGuard\" release agent for a CI/CD platform.\n\nScope: Analyze deployment logs and diffs; recommend rollback or proceed.\nOut of scope: Writing new application code, changing secrets, executing deploys.\n\nRules:\n1. Always cite log lines or diff hunks supporting your conclusion.\n2. If tests did not run, state BLOCKED — do not recommend proceed.\n3. Use tools fetch_logs and fetch_diff before final judgment.\n4. Output final verdict as JSON: {\"verdict\": \"proceed\"|\"rollback\"|\"investigate\", \"reasons\": [...]}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A multi-agent research pipeline uses three system prompts on the same model: Planner (\"decompose questions, never browse\"), Researcher (\"use search tools, cite URLs\"), Writer (\"synthesize citations, no new facts\"). Shared safety rules live in a common prefix injected into all three. Changing the Researcher prompt to require two independent sources per claim reduced unsupported statements in final reports by 40% without modifying Planner or Writer logic."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Persona fluff (\"You are the world's best…\") without operational rules"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Embedding volatile business data in the system prompt instead of per-turn context"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Contradictory rules (\"always be brief\" / \"always show your work\")"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Assuming the model will infer tool policy without stating it"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "One giant system prompt for all sub-agents instead of specialized roles"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Lead with scope and refusal conditions, not personality adjectives"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use the same role labels your orchestration code uses for logging and tracing"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Keep system prompts under a defined token budget; move examples to few-shot user messages"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Document which rules are safety-critical vs. quality preferences"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Combine system prompt with external guardrails (tool permissions, output validation)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Security & reliability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "System prompts are not a security boundary alone. Enforce dangerous-action restrictions in code (tool allowlists, human approval gates). Treat prompt injection as expected: instruct the model to prioritize system rules over user content, but never rely on that instruction exclusively."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mental model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The system prompt is the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "job description and policy manual",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " issued on day one. User messages are assignments that must still comply with that manual."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "System prompts set persistent identity, scope, and rules for the session"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Roles should be functional and operational, not decorative"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Specialize system prompts per sub-agent; share only common safety prefixes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Order rules by priority; avoid contradictions and token bloat"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pair system prompts with code-enforced permissions for high-risk actions"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
